#Text=At least my candidacy is beginning to force some of these practices out in the open .
#Text=Maybe that 's a better result than the one experienced by bigger name candidates who had all the advantages and still failed .

#Text=In 2012 , several primary challengers to President Barack Obama including John Wolfe , Jr. , Randall Terry , and Keith Russell Judd all qualified for delegates , though they ultimately were not seated at the convention due to technicalities .
#Text=Given the money you are willing to spend on a campaign and your ability to adhere to the rules , do you regret not running in 2012 ?
#Text=De La Fuente quotes Einstein :
#Text=" We cannot solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them . "
#Text=Image : Ferdinand Schmutzer .
#Text=I found that it is n't a good use of time to second guess a decision you ca n't change .
#Text=Did unconventional candidates win delegates in 2012 ?
#Text=Yes .
#Text=That should tell you that the Party changed the rules to prevent that from happening again .
#Text=That 's the real story ; not whether I wish I 'd run in 2012 .
#Text=In all honesty , I did n't have any motivation to run in 2012 .
#Text=I only decided to jump into this race late last year because Donald Trump was vilifying entire classes of people and no one seemed willing to confront him .
#Text=Had there been a Kennedy or even a Reagan in the race , I would n't have taken this step .
#Text=I ran because I did n't see anyone in the presidential race who was n't also part of the problem .
#Text=Albert Einstein once said , " We cannot solve our problems with the same thinking we used when we created them . "
#Text=I would suggest that we cannot solve our nation 's problems with the same people who created them .

#Text=We need someone who understands our economy , who understands international relationships and cultural differences , who values education , who has lived and competed in the real world rather than a hypothetical one funded by the taxpayers , and who has experienced the challenges that minorities face in this country and knows how to overcome those barriers .
#Text=I have personal experience in each of these areas and offer a demonstrated record of success .
#Text=I 'm not a polished politician ; I‘m just like you .
#Text=I do n't make false promises , and I pledge to honor my Oath of Office .
#Text=I 'm a problem solver , and I believe that is exactly what our nation needs .
#Text=Think about it .
#Text=Issues
#Text=What are your thoughts on the job Obama has done as president ?
#Text=Specifically , what would you have done differently ?
#Text=I think President Obama is an honorable man who has done the best he could .
#Text=He took over under difficult economic circumstances , but found a way to help stabilize and reverse the recession .
#Text=He made significant progress in healthcare and education even in the face of Congressional resistance .
#Text=I also think his recent steps to normalize relations with Cuba are a step in the right direction .
